						<p>This is damaged and dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka [1431], Śukla, Māgha, ba. 1[4], Śivarātri</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1510 February 7 Thursday</hi> (not verifiable). It records that <hi rend="bold">Kṛishṇarāya-Mahārāya</hi> made a gift of the village <hi rend="bold">Malukaṇa</hi> for his own well-being.</p>						

